The construction works for the Citizens School Dubai in the United Arab Emirates, which will be double the size of all other schools within its catchment area, are almost complete. The project has been designed by Godwin Austen Johnson (GAJ), the largest and longest-established UK architectural and design practice, headquartered in the UAE, and sets to follow the UK National Curriculum. To also provide an “experience-based, inclusive curriculum” the school will also follow its custom-built curriculum known as the “Citizens Tapestry”. Citizens School Dubai is projected to hold a capacity of well about 2’600 children. The project will offer students, a 1,250 meters squared multi-purpose hall, 2,900 meters squared open recreational and playing area, and rugby and football pitches that adhere to World Rugby stand as well as FIFA standards. Also Read: Construction of Creek Views I at Dubai Healthcare City in Dubai, UAE, Almost Complete The campus will also feature a six-lane semi-covered swimming pool as well as a dedicated dining area specifically for primary school students. The main contractor of the project is Intermass, the flagship company and one of the most prominent construction companies in the UAE, and alongside its designers, focused on placing special attention on the layout and design in ensuring that parents and students who seek special educational help do not feel left out. The groundbreaking event for the Citizens School Dubai Project was done in July 2019, however, due to the COVID-19 pandemic, the project faced a spectrum of obstacles. These obstacles caused the project to slow down construction in July 2020 and later on resumed in September 2021. The project is expected to be completed and the campus’s doors opened for students by September this year. Tuition fees for the school will range from $9,809 to $14,167 and the fess will be inclusive of all educational resources.